= Comments =

In the SVD accuracy benchmark it is possible for a zero matrix to be created as an input.  When a zero matrix is an input the score will always be a NaN.  As a result all SVD algorithms have a 90% metric value of NaN in the small case.  This problem will be fixed in the next release.
